&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Client Technology Staging Associate is excellent entry level position to jump start your career in IT! As a CTS Associate you&#39;ll be responsible for end-to-end device provisioning and multi-device staging in support of the Abacus client base. This role combines hands-on PC building and imaging with user onboarding/offboarding and the configuration of additional client hardware such as mobile devices, phones, and select network-enabled equipment. This position is client-facing in impact and highly visible within the organization. It requires precision, strong communication skills, technical depth across Windows and cloud environments, and a process-driven mindset. While exposure to network-connected devices is expected, this role does not require advanced network engineering responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Associates in this role are expected to execute standardized build processes while also identifying opportunities to improve efficiency through automation and scripting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PC Build, Imaging &amp;amp; Hardware Configuration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and configure laptops and desktop PCs using Abacus standard procurement and build processes&lt;br&gt;• Execute imaging workflows (PXE, USB, or automated tools)&lt;br&gt;• Stage devices according to Abacus and client-specific checklists&lt;br&gt;• Install and configure Windows and macOS operating systems&lt;br&gt;• Configure BIOS settings, drivers, and firmware updates as required&lt;br&gt;• Troubleshoot hardware issues including GPUs, USB devices, driver conflicts, and OS-level errors&lt;br&gt;• Validate successful configuration prior to shipment&lt;/li&gt;
